N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 12 ยง 263.21 - Sufficiency of petition

State Regulations

No petition in a proceeding under section 705 of SERA
shall be dismissed for failure of the petitioner to set forth in the petition
all the information required, however, the hearing officer may, if necessary, require information not provided in the petition. Notes
